1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,680
{\an8}<i>I want to talk to her in private.</i>

2
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,600
{\an8}Nun!

3
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,800
{\an8}He's not my brother.

4
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:46,960
{\an8}<i>He's just the troublemaker of our family.</i>

5
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:50,080
{\an8}<i>Khanin is one of Fire Phoenix's members,</i>

6
00:02:50,920 --> 00:02:52,280
{\an8}just like Naruban.

7
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,320
{\an8}<i>The one who has to die…</i>

8
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,240
{\an8}…is Taiga.

9
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,520
{\an8}Death is so close to us.

10
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:01,240
{\an8}So close that sometimes,
we forget to watch out

11
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:03,320
{\an8}which direction
we're getting stabbed from.

12
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,720
Mr. Taiga.

13
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,800
Do you like it?

14
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:10,200
It's quite good.

15
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,080
I thought you'd say you like it.

16
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,840
You have no business here.

17
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,200
Mom,

18
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:48,080
this is Ratee. She's a friend of mine.

19
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:50,040
She owns the café on the first floor.

20
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,040
Good afternoon.

21
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,480
Good afternoon.

22
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:57,640
I'd like to treat you all to a coffee.

23
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:00,080
I'll have a server come
and take your orders.

24
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:01,160
Thank you.

25
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:02,120
Oh.

26
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,920
Then, may I order for Ms. Nun first?

27
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,360
One salted caramel affogato, please.

28
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:08,920
Rin,

29
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,520
go make me a coffee.

30
00:04:16,880 --> 00:04:18,079
I said go.

31
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,560
Prepare the data
of our clients on every platform.

32
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,520
I'm going downstairs
to talk to the IT team.

33
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,400
Why are you here?

34
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,480
I'm here to support you, Taiga.

35
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,680
Ratee, please.

36
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,880
I know.

37
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,040
Don't worry. Just go back to work.

38
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,280
Ms. Nun, it's your turn.

39
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,240
Was it good?

40
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:43,480
Why'd you come out here, sir?

41
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,480
I'm going to talk to the IT team. Why?

42
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:50,200
You should go back to your office,
or go home.

43
00:05:51,280 --> 00:05:52,360
Why?

44
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Uncle Punlop,

45
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,280
what are you doing here?

46
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,360
Mr. Naruban is being targeted.

47
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:08,280
I had your driver come pick you up.
Please go home.

48
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,960
Please go now. I told your driver
to wait at the entrance.

49
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:31,680
{\an8}PLEASE DO NOT LEAN ON ELEVATOR BUTTONS

50
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,040
Ugh.

51
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,800
Ugh.

52
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:26,760
Where's Rin?

53
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:29,320
Why's she taking so long? I need a coffee.

54
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,600
Ms. Nun,

55
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,200
would you like to try our coffee?

56
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,800
- Ms. Nun!
- Are you alright?

57
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,160
Ms. Nun, are you alright?

58
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,520
Are you alright?

59
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,960
- Are you hurt?
- You did that on purpose, didn't you?

60
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,400
Did you? Huh?

61
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,160
I didn't mean it.

62
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:00,880
What happened, honey?

63
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,320
She tripped me on purpose, Mom.

64
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,880
I didn't mean it!

65
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,240
Please excuse us.

66
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:45,240
Are you hurt?

67
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,440
- My dress got a little stained.
- Was it hot?

68
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,280
Rin!

69
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,240
Are you okay?

70
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:23,840
Don't get up yet. You're hurt, right?

71
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:33,120
Damn it!

72
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:36,920
So close. That Naruban,

73
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,320
that Fire Phoenix guy would've been dead!

74
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,600
Taiga!

75
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,960
Taiga! Taiga!

76
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,840
I just wanted to see you while you work.

77
00:09:52,920 --> 00:09:54,920
Nunnapat isn't a good model
for your clothes anyway.

78
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,680
But this is my work!

79
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:04,240
Why are you so childish, Ratee?

80
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,000
Fine,

81
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:09,240
I admit it. I hate her guts.

82
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,000
That's why I had Techut take me there.

83
00:10:11,760 --> 00:10:15,040
Well, if Nannapat
didn't get so close to you…

84
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,400
I'm sorry.

85
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,640
You have to know
I hate those people at 3C.

86
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,400
This has got to end someday.

87
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,400
You have to think about our future too.

88
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:37,160
You don't care
about my love for you at all, do you?

89
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:43,800
Do you love for your own happiness

90
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,600
or for your partner's happiness?

91
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,640
- Stay out of this.
- I can't.

92
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,920
Taiga's doing everything

93
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:55,200
to find someone to pay
for his dad's death.

94
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,400
You love him, yet you never understood

95
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,960
or stayed patient
for the sake of his wish.

96
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,680
Only moody, self-centered, worthless girls

97
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:08,520
would use love as an excuse
to get what they want.

98
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,200
Ratee.

99
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:16,000
You have no right to criticize me.

100
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:39,200
Taiga's a good guy, but I'm not.

101
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,960
I just say it as I see it.

102
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:45,600
Plus, I don't need to be polite
with selfish girls like you.

103
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,600
Stop using true love

104
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:52,080
as an excuse
to control someone else's life, okay?

105
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:17,320
Don't worry about her.

106
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:22,040
You've got bigger things
to worry about than her.

107
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:26,080
Today, while you were at work,

108
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,800
I hacked the cameras at 3C.

109
00:12:38,280 --> 00:12:39,280
Khanin.

110
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,520
And who's this?

111
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,040
No idea.

112
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:51,640
I tried other angles,
but I couldn't find his face.

113
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,600
It's as if he knew
how to avoid all the cameras,

114
00:12:55,120 --> 00:12:58,200
and all the footage during that time
got wiped clean.

115
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:02,760
Someone must've ordered it
to be deleted for sure.

116
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,600
Someone who could do that…

117
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,800
Naruban.

118
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,760
Here, let me help you.

119
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,960
How'd the uniform shoot go?

120
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,920
It's still not quite done.

121
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,680
How long will that designer
keep working for us?

122
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,520
You don't seem to like Mr. Taiga.

123
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:35,200
Tell your daughter to end it.
Pay him and get rid of him.

124
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,360
But the project isn't done yet.

125
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:39,600
Or should I fire him myself?

126
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,800
What's the cause, then?

127
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,280
If you fire him without cause,
it can damage our company.

128
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:48,040
Well, a good cause
is that I hate his work.

129
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,800
Pay him and fire him.

130
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:54,280
I don't want him to show up at 3C again,
no matter what the reason.

131
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:58,040
If no one gives orders,
I'll handle it myself.

132
00:14:11,560 --> 00:14:12,720
Sit.

133
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,320
It's nice to sit outside sometimes.

134
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:23,080
TAIGA - INCOMING CALL

135
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,360
Mr. Taiga?

136
00:14:29,760 --> 00:14:31,160
TAIGA - INCOMING CALL

137
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:32,920
Mr. Taiga again!

138
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,720
He must be worried about you.

139
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:40,280
There's no need to be.

140
00:14:54,520 --> 00:14:56,640
<i>Please leave a message after the tone…</i>

141
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,920
I need your help.

142
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,440
I want to know Rin's friend,

143
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:11,200
the one she's closest to.

144
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:29,320
{\an8}BANGPAKOK 3 HOSPITAL
BREATHING AS ONE

145
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,360
Are you okay?

146
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,240
Here.

147
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,240
Relax.

148
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:05,599
By the time those two finish talking,
we'll have finished both cups.

149
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:09,079
Rin's going to kill me.

150
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:12,400
If I didn't see
that Mr. Taiga kept calling,

151
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,599
I would've kept quiet.

152
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:15,000
Ah.

153
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:17,560
Here,

154
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:18,520
go ahead.

155
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,400
Ow!

156
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,680
How'd you end up here?

157
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,320
I fell down the stairs
and sprained my ankle.

158
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,440
How'd you get here?

159
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:58,640
Must've been Aru.

160
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,280
Are you badly hurt?

161
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:04,000
I'm okay.

162
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,240
Huh.

163
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,160
Nno broken limbs.

164
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,480
Now I believe that you're okay.

165
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,840
You still hit just as hard as ever.

166
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:34,840
Are you cold?

167
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:03,240
Nun, trust me.

168
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:07,440
Your dad has reason
for not wanting Taiga to work at 3C.

169
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,680
Is hatred

170
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,200
a reason that makes sense?

171
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:14,400
No one can be good at everything
or win every time.

172
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,080
Sometimes,

173
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:19,560
silence is the best solution.

174
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,880
Don't do anything.

175
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:26,160
I'll take care of Taiga's situation.

176
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,240
Here.

177
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,040
You can be on your way now.

178
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:07,640
Mr. Taiga, why don't you come upstairs
and have something to drink?

179
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,480
Let's go.

180
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:25,680
My place isn't so big, but it's still

181
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,440
a "home sweet home".

182
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:32,440
Whoa, your light.
You use that for your livestreams?

183
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:36,800
If you use two more of those,
you'll glow up so hard,

184
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:39,320
- and your sales will go way up.
- Whoa!

185
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,320
Do you have one? Can you give me one?

186
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:44,080
Thank you for the ride.
I'll stop bothering you now.

187
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,040
I'm free today.

188
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,560
I'm also super free.

189
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:49,120
Then, can you go buy me a light?

190
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Ow!

191
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:56,880
Mr. Taiga,

192
00:20:57,480 --> 00:21:01,520
would you like to try designing
a new collection that's more street style?

193
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,800
We don't need to use your brand.

194
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,600
We can sell it under my brand.

195
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:08,800
We could try and sell it
on my livestreams.

196
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:10,040
Want to give it a try?

197
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,960
That's some good marketing.

198
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:16,520
No wonder you invited us in.

199
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:21,600
I'm a fan of his brand too, you know?

200
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,640
Sure.

201
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,000
But

202
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:27,240
I can't really afford it,
so I can only shop with my eyes.

203
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:31,000
- Should I try creating a few designs?
- You don't need to.

204
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,080
Yes, please! That'd be perfect.

205
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:35,760
We could make it a limited edition.
Maybe sell only ten.

206
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:38,760
Surely, everyone will want it,
and the price will skyrocket!

207
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:41,120
Let me see.

208
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:44,280
- What?!
- Your brain is amazing.

209
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,920
Amazing. What a great seller.

210
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,360
Well, it's hard to make money.

211
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:51,080
I see an opportunity right in front of me,

212
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:53,000
so, of course, I have to seize it.

213
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:55,960
Actually, it's an interesting idea.

214
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,760
I'll design for you.

215
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,400
Whoa!

216
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:03,560
For free, right?

217
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:08,480
Honestly, I can't afford to hire
someone on your level like 3C can.

218
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,160
- It's free.
- Don't!

219
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:12,880
And feel free to sell it under your brand.

220
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:16,280
Can I hold your hand, please?

221
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:19,840
Thank you! Thank you so much!

222
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,920
Leave him alone, Aru.

223
00:22:22,560 --> 00:22:24,760
It's fine. It'll be fun.

224
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:26,120
See?

225
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:28,320
Well, aren't you sweet?

226
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:31,000
- Let me thank you again.
- Hey, thank me instead.

227
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,160
You've thanked him enough.

228
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:33,480
- Please?
- What?

229
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:35,080
Do you even know how to design?

230
00:22:35,680 --> 00:22:37,000
No, not at all.

231
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,040
Model for me, then.

232
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:43,440
- How about this dress!
- Model?

233
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:46,720
Yas, sis!

234
00:22:48,360 --> 00:22:49,360
<i>You need a new model?</i>

235
00:22:50,720 --> 00:22:51,560
Yeah?

236
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:00,560
Please don't forget our promise.

237
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:03,800
I won't. I'll send you a design tonight.

238
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:06,920
He's making me fall again.

239
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,480
Hey, don't fall for me.

240
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:10,960
I don't want to carry your stuff.

241
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,000
Not you!

242
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,720
Leave already. Go!

243
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:30,320
- I'm such a big fan!
- I'm going now. Bye.

244
00:23:31,080 --> 00:23:32,560
Bye-bye.

245
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,920
What do you think we'll gain
from those two?

246
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:48,040
I want to know more about Rin.

247
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:51,280
But if she finds the bug, we're screwed.

248
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:54,520
She's smart. She'll surely
be able to tell it's us.

249
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,960
I'll take my chances.

250
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:00,640
Rin's the closest person to Naruban.

251
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,840
We might find a link
between Khanin and Fire Phoenix.

252
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:06,760
Khanin wants revenge
on the Fire Phoenix guys,

253
00:24:06,840 --> 00:24:10,680
yet he never told you
he's also one of them.

254
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,120
He claimed he knew your mom

255
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:17,040
and told you he got framed, forced off
the police force, and also hunted.

256
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:18,640
Now I don't even know

257
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:22,640
what to believe from Khanin anymore.

258
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,320
Oh well,

259
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,720
at least you two share the same goals.

260
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:33,560
Get close to Naruban
and destroy Fire Phoenix.

261
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:36,920
The only problem is…

262
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,480
Rin.

263
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,440
They released a new music video!

264
00:24:46,960 --> 00:24:49,360
It's from Ryu Dragon!

265
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:50,680
Here we go!

266
00:24:54,160 --> 00:24:55,880
Here we go.

267
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:01,600
Look, look!

268
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:03,600
Isn't he cute?

269
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:06,200
Is he as cute in person?

270
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:09,520
Right? I knew it.

271
00:25:09,600 --> 00:25:10,840
Look!

272
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:13,640
They filmed it on a beach.

273
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:18,440
We use 3C-Coin to make huge profits,

274
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,880
then we spend those huge profits

275
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:23,520
so we can have the world
in the palm of our hands.

276
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:32,480
I hope you don't think
Nun's stupid "new uniform" project

277
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:34,600
can ever help us grow bigger.

278
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,360
I never agreed with it. You know that.

279
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,080
Then you should fire Taiga.

280
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:44,760
Trust me. I'll use my power
to build our empire.

281
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:13,280
I hope you don't think I'm intruding.

282
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:17,560
I see you really gave your all for 3C.

283
00:26:19,040 --> 00:26:21,640
But it seems like 3C
doesn't welcome me anymore.

284
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:26,640
I apologize on everyone's behalf.

285
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:29,080
I hope all the chaos here

286
00:26:29,160 --> 00:26:31,520
didn't make you want to leave us.

287
00:26:32,280 --> 00:26:35,720
I'll make sure my work's finished.
Don't worry.

288
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:39,080
Now we just need the uniform
to be finished,

289
00:26:39,160 --> 00:26:41,720
and as for the small tasks,
like promoting the videos,

290
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:45,600
you don't need to do that.
Let's leave it to an ad agency.

291
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,360
So you're here to fire me.

292
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:50,640
To be honest,

293
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:53,920
I don't want any more trouble
like yesterday.

294
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,680
The woman who came with my son, Techut,

295
00:26:58,440 --> 00:26:59,680
is she your friend?

296
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,800
Ratee won't be here again.

297
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:06,040
Please let me finish my work.

298
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:10,440
You want to handle the filming, don't you?

299
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,800
Yes.

300
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:16,320
Ms. Nun doesn't have
to model in it either.

301
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:20,040
We can have someone else do it.

302
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,400
I want Rin to model for me.

303
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:29,520
I don't know about that.
She's just an employee.

304
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:33,840
The clothes I design

305
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,400
must be worn by someone
who can present them best.

306
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:49,040
Mr. Taiga wants Rin to model
for 3C's uniform?

307
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:56,440
That way, we can get it over with.

308
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:05,280
You're not the loser here.

309
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,560
Your tears from today

310
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:19,240
will become a fire

311
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:23,320
that'll burn your enemies to the ground
until even their souls are gone.

312
00:28:52,880 --> 00:28:54,520
Are you sure you're fine?

313
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,720
Yes, I'm okay.

314
00:28:57,800 --> 00:28:59,120
And you?

315
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,560
I'm fine.

316
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,680
I’ve had more guards brought in.

317
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:08,840
Can I see all the cameras' footage?
I need to find that guy.

318
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:10,800
I ordered all of it to be deleted.

319
00:29:12,360 --> 00:29:16,040
If it got out,
it'll be bad for 3C's reputation.

320
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:24,120
Taiga will be out of here soon.

321
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:28,480
Until then, watch his every move.

322
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:31,280
Don't let Taiga damage 3C again.

323
00:29:33,720 --> 00:29:34,760
Yes, sir.

324
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:52,000
<i>Taiga will be out of here soon.</i>

325
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:54,160
<i>Watch his every move.</i>

326
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:56,200
<i>Don't let Taiga damage 3C again.</i>

327
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:21,760
I just told Mrs. Giranun

328
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,160
that I want you to model for my clothes.

329
00:30:29,720 --> 00:30:31,600
- Well, I--
- Don't want to?

330
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:41,200
Please don't refuse, Rin.

331
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:44,440
I'll show everyone

332
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,320
that no one should look down on others.

333
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:01,080
Taiga's trying to turn
the spotlight on me.

334
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,280
Try to earn his trust for now, Rin.

335
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,400
Pretend you're a decoy.

336
00:31:05,480 --> 00:31:07,960
Squeeze everything you can out of Taiga

337
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,480
before you deal with him.

338
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:23,600
You had Rin monitor Taiga?

339
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:26,720
Aren't you afraid
they'll team up and betray us?

340
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:29,560
Do you know

341
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:33,040
what traitors are afraid of the most?

342
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:38,040
Traitors

343
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:40,600
are afraid of other traitors.

344
00:31:51,240 --> 00:31:52,840
I need to get away from 3C.

345
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:55,000
Naruban found out about you?

346
00:31:55,600 --> 00:31:57,040
They're suspecting me,

347
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:00,200
so they're using my work as an excuse.

348
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:03,280
- We need to hurry and finish the job.
- No.

349
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:06,000
I'll handle it.

350
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,760
Naruban's life is mine to take.

351
00:32:08,840 --> 00:32:10,440
You?

352
00:32:10,520 --> 00:32:13,120
You had so many chances, but never did it.
What are you waiting for?

353
00:32:14,440 --> 00:32:17,280
I want to destroy them completely.

354
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,720
Fire Phoenix will have nothing left
but its name.

355
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,560
Here.

356
00:32:30,320 --> 00:32:32,600
It's Mr. Taiga's design!

357
00:32:32,680 --> 00:32:33,840
Hold it for a sec.

358
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:45,000
Can… Can I scream?

359
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,480
He really gave me all these?

360
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:54,680
And he won't charge me?

361
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:56,720
All of those are free.

362
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:03,120
Wow!

363
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:05,800
I'm so freaking happy!

364
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,200
All my superstitions paid off.

365
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:11,800
They're so, so pretty!

366
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,520
You'll be selling like crazy, Aru.

367
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:25,160
Can you tell Mr. Taiga

368
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:28,440
that I want to pay for his designs?
I don't accept freebies.

369
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,320
How will you pay him?

370
00:33:32,400 --> 00:33:36,240
How about
a huge set of barbecue or hot pot?

371
00:33:36,320 --> 00:33:37,680
I can be free any day. Let me know.

372
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,280
- Totally worth it.
- Yeah.

373
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:42,880
Sure, sure. Gotta go.

374
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,280
- Tell him for me.
- Okay.

375
00:34:04,680 --> 00:34:07,720
That scumbag of a husband. So ungrateful.

376
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,199
So untameable!

377
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:13,159
I treat your mom and sister so well,

378
00:34:13,239 --> 00:34:16,199
yet you betrayed me
and went to see your ex!

379
00:34:17,480 --> 00:34:20,520
Why'd you go see her?
She's poorer than me.

380
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:21,760
Why?!

381
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:54,159
What's wrong?

382
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:56,800
You've been frowning for an hour now.

383
00:34:58,360 --> 00:34:59,560
I don't want to model.

384
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:01,360
Really, Rin?

385
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:05,760
If I were you, I'd set off firecrackers
at ten temples to celebrate.

386
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,920
I'd offer a dance,
a pig's head, Thai clothing,

387
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:10,120
zebras, or anything to the gods.

388
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,200
I'd even run naked.

389
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:16,360
Rin,

390
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:19,200
you think Taiga's
asking you to do it just for fun

391
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,640
or just because he's bored?

392
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:22,720
You know it's a big deal, right?

393
00:35:22,800 --> 00:35:25,760
You'll be the face of 3C, for God's sake!

394
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:28,680
You'll get to wear a pretty outfit
Mr. Taiga designed too.

395
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:30,800
Do you know how lucky you are?

396
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:34,360
Do you want to do it instead?

397
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,280
What?

398
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,400
Can I really do that?

399
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,200
As if Mr. Taiga would be okay with that.

400
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:49,800
Hey,

401
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:54,840
this is your chance.
Don't let it get away.

402
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:57,800
Think of it as a nice life experience.

403
00:36:02,520 --> 00:36:04,880
How about you ask them

404
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:08,200
if I can be there at the shoot,
so you'll be more relaxed?

405
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,560
Perfect.

406
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:14,960
Then, you need to practice your walk.

407
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,800
- Get up, get up!
- Ugh!

408
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:21,720
As a top supermodel

409
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,760
and the queen of the runway,
I'll train you myself.

410
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:29,440
Hey! Get up, will you?

411
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,560
I'm going to sleep.

412
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:32,240
- You're sleeping?
- I'm so sleepy.

413
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:34,920
You need to practice your walk,
so you'll really shine.

414
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:36,400
- Don't sleep yet!
- Let me sleep!

415
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,680
No! Come on.

416
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,600
Don't fake sleep now. Get up!

417
00:36:39,680 --> 00:36:41,000
- No.
- Come on!

418
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:05,760
Done!

419
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,760
You're done? Let me see.

420
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:11,880
You're so pretty!

421
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:13,800
You have to smile, okay?

422
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:17,040
Smile a lot,
like you're lighting up the world,

423
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:19,800
like you're proud of working at 3C.

424
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:26,480
Smile. Come on.

425
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:48,040
Go on. Do your hair.

426
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:50,960
Smile.

427
00:38:58,240 --> 00:38:59,680
Don't you want to go down there?

428
00:39:06,520 --> 00:39:10,760
Then, I'll go and keep you updated
in real-time.

429
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:31,000
So pretty!

430
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:34,080
Looking fabulous as the face of 3C!

431
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,520
Everyone at 3C is pretty.

432
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:40,280
Give me a confident smile,
like you know you're the prettiest.

433
00:39:40,880 --> 00:39:43,280
Okay? Walk to the center there,

434
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:45,480
then look straight into the camera.

435
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,600
Okay? Ready?

436
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:49,040
Let's go. Please, take her.

437
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:51,040
You got this! Come on.

438
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:12,280
Beautiful! Just like that, Rin.

439
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,920
You look so pretty!

440
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,560
Yeah, just like that.

441
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:32,760
Aru.

442
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:37,200
Sun?

443
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:40,400
How'd you get here?

444
00:40:41,960 --> 00:40:43,440
They're shooting her?

445
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:24,880
Beautiful.

446
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:29,920
Keep walking.

447
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:37,760
Okay. Side angle, please.

448
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:44,200
I got it. Okay.

449
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:54,960
Now give us your right side.

450
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:58,320
Beautiful!

451
00:42:00,120 --> 00:42:02,120
Just like that. Be confident.

452
00:42:21,360 --> 00:42:24,440
Can we do one more?
Give me more confidence.

453
00:42:29,120 --> 00:42:30,480
Now pose.

454
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:31,720
Beautiful.

455
00:42:56,560 --> 00:42:57,480
Hold on.

456
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:09,240
Turn around.

457
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:18,200
You look pretty.

458
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:37,160
What?

459
00:43:45,320 --> 00:43:46,280
Taiga.

460
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:47,640
Taiga!

461
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:50,960
Huh?

462
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:52,800
We need to leave.

463
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:00,960
Are you okay?

464
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:20,520
Get out of the way.
I told you, get out of the way!

465
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:21,600
- Move!
- Pat!

466
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:26,600
You love her so much, don't you?

467
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:30,120
You love each other so much, huh? Die!

468
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:36,280
- No!
- No!

469
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:38,440
- Hey!
- No!

470
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:40,400
Pat!

471
00:44:43,720 --> 00:44:44,680
Sun.

472
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,400
It hurts.

473
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:10,080
{\an8}Aru, gorgeous!

474
00:45:12,200 --> 00:45:14,000
{\an8}I can do a lot worse than that.

475
00:45:14,080 --> 00:45:15,720
{\an8}The bullets were directed at me only.

476
00:45:15,800 --> 00:45:17,000
{\an8}Who do you think did it?

477
00:45:17,080 --> 00:45:19,320
{\an8}I don't know. Do you?

478
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:21,800
{\an8}My dad died because of Fire Phoenix.

479
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:23,760
{\an8}Then why aren’t you searching
for the truth?

480
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:25,240
{\an8}<i>The mask contains</i>

481
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:27,800
{\an8}<i>the code to all the information</i>
<i>of every member.</i>

482
00:45:27,880 --> 00:45:29,560
{\an8}<i>If we can steal Naruban's mask,</i>

483
00:45:29,640 --> 00:45:32,280
{\an8}then we can get
to the core of Fire Phoenix.

484
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:06,520
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

